title: Blueberry Gorgonzola Salad
author: Katherine Emmons, North Oaks, MN,
copyright: Â© 2016 MyRecipes.com is part of the Time Inc. Food Collection and the Time Inc. Lifestyle Network. All Rights Reserved.
description: From Katherine Emmons, North Oaks, MN The sublime combination of sweet fruit and salty blue cheese means you can keep the rest of the salad simple. White balsamic vinegar gives the dressing a light flavor.
directions:
1. In a large bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, and salt. Add lettuces and blueberries and toss to coat.

2. Divide mixture among 4 salad plates. Sprinkle with pine nuts and gorgonzola, and grind pepper over each salad.
ingredients:
1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil
3 tablespoons white balsamic vinegar
1/2 teaspoon kosher salt
10 cup loosely packed mixed lettuces (3 oz.)
1 cup blueberries
1/4 cup toasted pine nuts
4 ounces gorgonzola cheese, crumbled
Pepper
